      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The primary QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) must be directly linked to the regulatory acceptance criterion and clinically relevant hemolysis threshold.",
      "rationale": "RH is defined as the ratio of device NIH to predicate NIH. This metric is used in FDA guidance for 510(k) hemolysis comparisons. Clinical relevance is established by correlation with plasma free hemoglobin thresholds in published literature. QoI relevance requirement satisfied."
