      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, model form uncertainty need not be formally quantified; selection of turbulence and hemolysis sub-models with literature justification is sufficient.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published benchmark performance for rotating blood pump geometries. Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model applied with published constants. Formal model form uncertainty quantification deferred per MRL 2 scope. Factor recorded as not-assessed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters (fluid properties, boundary conditions, geometry) must be traceable to measurement records or published reference values with stated uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Fluid viscosity and density measured at 37°C using calibrated rheometer (±1.2%). Pump geometry digitized from CMM measurements with ±0.02 mm tolerance. Inlet velocity profiles derived from experimental PIV data archived in dataset morrison-cpb-experimental-validation-dataset-001. All inputs traceable to measurement records. The experimental dataset carries a dataVintage of 2025-10-22, predating the model revision on 2025-11-14 by approximately three weeks. The intervening model update refined the near-wall mesh topology in the volute region to improve shear stress resolution; the team judged this change not material to the inlet boundary condition data or fluid property measurements sourced from the dataset, and no formal re-validation against the updated mesh was conducted. Achieved level meets requirement."
    },
